post_text: Good Morning this is superintendent Jeff Vetter with a correction regarding physicals that appeared in the recent newsletter. All students entering kindergarten and seventh grade, or any students enrolling from out of state are required to get a physical to attend school. Only ninth graders planning to participate in activities must get an activity physical for the 2020-2021 school year. Also please contact the school for students riding the bus staying for the after school program.

post_text: This is superintendent Jeff Vetter, with an update on physicals. After consulting with the Department of Education and the Nebraska School Activities Association today it has been clarified that incoming Kindergarten and 7th grade students will need a physical to begin school in the fall. 8th graders will not need a sports physical if they had one on file from the 2019-2020 school year. Thanks and have a great day!

Thanks and have a great day!

post_text: Our teachers were hard at work today, prepping lessons for our students during this school closure.
text: Our teachers were hard at work today, prepping lessons for our students during this school closure.

post_text: Pleasanton Public Schools and Daycare will be closed beginning tomorrow through Friday, March 27th as a result of the recent announcements by Governor Ricketts and Education Commissioner Matt Bloomstedt made earlier today. We will be posting a more concise message concerning the closure on our school website. We will be meeting with staff to decide how to best continue the education of our students and will provide that information as soon as practicable.

We will be meeting with staff to decide how to best continue the education of our students and will provide that information as soon as practicable.

This spring the Pleasanton Bulldogs will be working on a project to create record boards for the following activities boys/girls basketball, football, golf, track and field, volleyball, wrestling, and for anyone that received a “27” or higher on their ACT. But in order to complete this project we need your help.

If you believe you have a record or know of someone that has a record please bring in any evidence to prove your claim to Pleasanton Public Schools. Examples of evidence would be dated newspaper articles, old scorebooks, dated pictures. Unfortunately we will not be able to use word of mouth as a source it must be documented. If you or someone you know scored a “27” or higher on the ACT please contact Pleasanton Public Schools and we will look in the student records to confirm. We are hoping to have these record boards completed over the summer.

Please send all information to Pleasanton Public Schools by May 8, 2020. If you have any questions please contact Casey Loomis at Pleasanton Public Schools. Thank you and GO BULLDOGS!!!!

THANK YOU FOR SUPPORTING Pleasanton students!

post_text:
Pleasanton School Board Vacancy
Pleasanton Public Schools will have three school board positions up for election/re-election in the 2020 election cycle. Two incumbent school board members have indicated their intention to run for re-election, while a third board member has decided not to run for re-election.

Anyone interested in filing to run for one of our school board positions may pick up the necessary forms at the Buffalo County Election office or from the Superintendent of Pleasanton Public Schools.

The first day a person may file for office to have their names included on the 2020 election ballot is December 2, 2019. Incumbents have until February 18, 2020 to file for office on the primary ballot. Non-incumbents have until March 2, 2020 to file for office on the primary election. The statewide primary election is on May 12, 2020

Platte River Preps December Athlete of the Month

December Winner:
Isabelle Paitz, Pleasanton Basketball

Belle, a Junior, is the leading scorer on a top five team in Class D1 averaging 10 points per game, and 4.5 rebounds per game. She nabs two steals and dishes out 1.5 assists per game. She shoots just south of 40% per game while leading the Bulldogs to a undefeated start to the season at 8-0.
